			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Sorry if this is bloggish.<br />
<br />
I had two interviews today.  One was a phone interview, the other was in person.<br />
<br />
The phone interview went great, the company sounds really interesting, and I was told I'd be brought in for an in person based on the positive phone experience.  I'm looking forward to proceeding with that one.<br />
<br />
The in person interview was passable.  The technical questions all seemed to be about stuff I have little to no experience with, and I was asked few if any questions about stuff I DO have experience with.  I did check, I meet the majority of the criteria they are looking for based on the job description, but they possibly were not quite clear.  Mainly, I was asked a lot of database stuff, and the database is not my strong suit.  Anyway, I told the recruiter to proceed to the next step if it is available, but I'm just not really sure that I want to.  Or rather, I'm not sure that I am all that interested in the job they described, especially as compared to the one I had the phone interview for.<br />
<br />
I think I might have told the recruiter to proceed simply based on the fact that it is 'a job' and I don't have one.  Anyone else ever had that happen?</div>

