			<description><![CDATA[Look at the following two links. 
 
Summary of the US Government's Financial Future 
http://www.whitehouse.gov/omb/financial/reports/citizens_guide.pdf 
 
Glenn Beck talking about Social Security, Medicare, Medicaid with the Comptroller General of the United States....]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Look at the following two links.<br />
<br />
Summary of the US Government's Financial Future<br />
<a href="http://www.whitehouse.gov/omb/financial/reports/citizens_guide.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.whitehouse.gov/omb/financ...zens_guide.pdf</a><br />
<br />
Glenn Beck talking about Social Security, Medicare, Medicaid with the Comptroller General of the United States.<br />
[media]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I-16u9x3tfE[/media]<br />
<br />
Presentation by the Comptroller General himself<br />
[media]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KjZBOCAgR64&amp;feature=related[/media]<br />
<br />
<br />
Do any of you plan on using Social Security, Medicare, or Medicaid in the future?  I recommend you don't think bargain on it.<br />
<br />
Here's some food for thought.<br />
<br />
- The US government owes $5 trillion to the public and $4 trillion to Social Security and other government trust funds.<br />
<br />
- In 2007, the US government budget was:<br />
<br />
Department of Defense - $665 billion<br />
Social Security - $626 billion<br />
Medicare and Medicaid - $556 billion<br />
Interest - $239 billion<br />
Other health - $111 billion<br />
Other government - $713 billion<br />
<br />
- Federal revenue over the past few years has been at 18% of GDP, regardless of tax levels.<br />
<br />
- To fully fund future obligations, $58 <b>trillion</b> needs to be invested now.  Current level: $0.<br />
<br />
- To prevent a disaster, it does seem that payroll taxes will need to be raised by at least 100%.  Would you like to pay 26% of your income in payroll taxes alone?  Or perhaps an increase in income tax of 74%?<br />
<br />
<br />
The US Comptroller General is doing a tour of states to warn them of the coming problems.  There is no precedent to this.<br />
<br />
How in the hell can anyone justify MORE government services, such as healthcare?  And on the same coin, how can anyone justifying tax cuts?  If anything, taxes need to be doubled unless people are willing to substantially reduce or eliminate SS, Medicare, and Medicaid.<br />
<br />
This is scary.  Remember, you <b>always</b> have to pay, whether it is now or later.  And it is coming.</div>

