			<title>Overall impressions from Preview Weekend?</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?t=60020&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Tue, 26 Aug 2008 13:28:56 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[So, those of you that were in the beta/preview weekend, what are your overall impressions?  Will the game have legs once it's released?  Or will it be another Age of Conan, with high initial sales, but rapidly dropping subs? 
 
My impressions - keep this in mind, I didn't get any characters over...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>So, those of you that were in the beta/preview weekend, what are your overall impressions?  Will the game have legs once it's released?  Or will it be another Age of Conan, with high initial sales, but rapidly dropping subs?<br />
<br />
My impressions - keep this in mind, I didn't get any characters over level 8 in the preview, but I played 7 different classes spread across both factions:<br />
<br />
Things I liked:<br />
<br />
The game has a lot of things to like about it.  For one thing, this doesn't feel like a dead world, like so many games - there is stuff going on.  In the dark elf area, you have armies marching off the Black Ark and going off to battle, there is fighting all around, with NPCs taking on mobs, etc.  It *feels* like a war zone, which it is.  Other starting areas were the same way.<br />
<br />
Public quests are great, but all the ones I took part in were pretty much the same template:  wave 1: kill 30-75 small mobs, wave 2: kill 8-10 harder mobs, wave3: kill a big baddie.  Maybe higher tiered public quests are different, and I hope so, or PQs will get old quick.  But I love the idea behind them, and the fact that you earn Influence points that you can use for rewards is great - if you are unlucky (like me) and always lose the rolls for gear, you can still get stuff from your influence points.<br />
<br />
Open groups - I didn't see any open groups this weekend, so I have no idea how they work, but they sound like a great idea.<br />
<br />
Things I didn't like:<br />
<br />
I am getting tired of games that "hold my hand" and tell me where to go.  Sure, quests are nice, and level-appropriate content is nice, but I miss the older free form games where you explored and moved around the world on your own.  Instead of doing 3 quests here, then moving to the next town and doing 8 quests there, then moving on, etc.  And I know, I don't have to do the quests, but the content is set up in a way to move you along a certain path, whether you do the quests in a given area or not.  There are things to like about this method, but it also feels restrictive to me.<br />
<br />
I'm not sure how long the game will last if there's not a lot of PvE content for people to consume.  PvP is fun, and it's good to have a game built around it, but after so many PvP battles it gets old and players will want something to do besides PvP.<br />
<br />
As good as the Public Quests are, I worry what's going to happen when server populations drop.  All the lower tier quests I took part in this weekend required groups to complete parts 2 and 3.  If there is no population in an area, those quests will go unfinished I think.  And that will be harder on new players who miss out on the initial wave of leveling.<br />
<br />
Overall I like the game and I will play it at least for the free month.  I'm concerned that the top tier content hasn't been shown yet, and the testers on that content are still under strict NDA - not a good sign - and if past games are any indication, there will be players ready for that content within a week or two of release.<br />
<br />
So, what are other peoples' thoughts? :)</div>

]]></content:encoded>
